Files:
- plugins/wikipedia/src/tools/get-page-views.ts (fix catch block, lines 41-47)

Context:
Current code (lines 40-47):
  try {
    const response = await fetchFromPage(url, { credentials: 'omit' });
    data = (await response.json()) as PageViewResponse;
  } catch (e) {
    if (e instanceof ToolError) throw e;
    throw ToolError.notFound(`Page view data not found for "${params.title}" in the given date range`);
  }

The issue: `response.json()` can throw SyntaxError if the Wikimedia API returns malformed JSON. This is caught and converted to notFound (wrong — the data failed to parse, not that it was not found).

Fix:
  } catch (e) {
    if (e instanceof ToolError) throw e;
    if (e instanceof SyntaxError) {
      throw ToolError.internal(`Failed to parse Wikimedia API response for "${params.title}"`);
    }
    throw ToolError.notFound(`Page view data not found for "${params.title}" in the given date range`);
  }

Note: fetchFromPage throws a ToolError on 404 (not a plain Error), so `e instanceof ToolError` at line 45 correctly handles real 404 notFound cases — they propagate as ToolError.notFound. The remaining non-ToolError exceptions are SyntaxError (bad JSON) or other network errors. Mapping SyntaxError to internal and keeping network errors as notFound (or also mapping to internal) is the correct fix.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the URL construction or fetchFromPage call
- The ToolError re-throw at line 45 must remain
- credentials: 'omit' is correct for the cross-origin Wikimedia API — do not change it
